trans-unit.source: Represents a composite geometry, composed of other <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Geometry"></xref> objects.
trans-unit.target: Representerer en sammensatt geometry, består av andre <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Geometry"> </xref> objekter.

trans-unit.source: Composite geometry objects can be created using a GeometryGroup, a <xref:System.Windows.Media.CombinedGeometry>, or by calling the static <xref:System.Windows.Media.Geometry> method <xref:System.Windows.Media.Geometry.Combine%2A>.
trans-unit.target: Sammensatte geometri-objekter kan opprettes ved hjelp av en GeometryGroup en <xref:System.Windows.Media.CombinedGeometry>, eller ved å kalle den statiske <xref:System.Windows.Media.Geometry>metoden <xref:System.Windows.Media.Geometry.Combine%2A>.</xref:System.Windows.Media.Geometry.Combine%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Media.Geometry> </xref:System.Windows.Media.CombinedGeometry>

trans-unit.source: A <xref:System.Windows.Media.CombinedGeometry> creates a composite geometry from exactly two geometry objects.
trans-unit.target: En <xref:System.Windows.Media.CombinedGeometry>oppretter en sammensatt geometri fra nøyaktig to geometri-objekter.</xref:System.Windows.Media.CombinedGeometry>

trans-unit.source: A GeometryGroup, on the other hand, creates a composite geometry from any number of geometry objects.
trans-unit.target: En GeometryGroup oppretter derimot, en sammensatt geometri fra antall geometri-objekter.

trans-unit.source: GeometryGroup uses the <xref:System.Windows.Media.GeometryGroup.FillRule%2A> property to specify how its geometry objects are combined.
trans-unit.target: GeometryGroup bruker den <xref:System.Windows.Media.GeometryGroup.FillRule%2A>til å angi hvordan geometri objektene kombineres.</xref:System.Windows.Media.GeometryGroup.FillRule%2A>

trans-unit.source: See [How to: Control the Fill of a Composite Shape](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md) for more information on using <xref:System.Windows.Media.GeometryGroup.FillRule%2A>.
trans-unit.target: Se [slik: kontrollere fyll for en sammensatt form](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md) for mer informasjon om hvordan du bruker <xref:System.Windows.Media.GeometryGroup.FillRule%2A>.</xref:System.Windows.Media.GeometryGroup.FillRule%2A>

trans-unit.source: Geometries can be combined in several ways: using a GeometryGroup, a <xref:System.Windows.Media.CombinedGeometry>, or the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Geometry.Combine%2A> method of the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Geometry> class.
trans-unit.target: Du kan kombinere geometri på flere måter: ved hjelp av en GeometryGroup en <xref:System.Windows.Media.CombinedGeometry>, eller <xref:System.Windows.Media.Geometry.Combine%2A>-metoden til <xref:System.Windows.Media.Geometry>klasse.</xref:System.Windows.Media.Geometry> </xref:System.Windows.Media.Geometry.Combine%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Media.CombinedGeometry>

trans-unit.source: - A GeometryGroup creates a composite geometry from one or more <xref:System.Windows.Media.Geometry> objects.
trans-unit.target: – En GeometryGroup oppretter en sammensatt geometri fra én eller flere <xref:System.Windows.Media.Geometry>objekter.</xref:System.Windows.Media.Geometry>

trans-unit.source: - A <xref:System.Windows.Media.CombinedGeometry> uses a specified boolean operation to combine the area described by two <xref:System.Windows.Media.Geometry> objects.
trans-unit.target: -A <xref:System.Windows.Media.CombinedGeometry>bruker en boolsk operasjon som er angitt til å kombinere diagramområdet som er beskrevet i to <xref:System.Windows.Media.Geometry>objekter.</xref:System.Windows.Media.Geometry> </xref:System.Windows.Media.CombinedGeometry>

trans-unit.source: - The static <xref:System.Windows.Media.Geometry.Combine%2A> method of the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Geometry> class behaves in exactly the same manner as the <xref:System.Windows.Media.CombinedGeometry> object.
trans-unit.target: -Statiske <xref:System.Windows.Media.Geometry.Combine%2A>metoden for den <xref:System.Windows.Media.Geometry>klassen håndterer på samme måte som den <xref:System.Windows.Media.CombinedGeometry>objektet.</xref:System.Windows.Media.CombinedGeometry> </xref:System.Windows.Media.Geometry> </xref:System.Windows.Media.Geometry.Combine%2A>

trans-unit.source: It is worth noting that a <xref:System.Windows.Media.GeometryCollection> is not itself a composite geometry, but is used by the GeometryGroup class to store <xref:System.Windows.Media.Geometry> objects.
trans-unit.target: Det er verdt å merke seg som en <xref:System.Windows.Media.GeometryCollection>er ikke en sammensatt geometry, men brukes av klassen GeometryGroup til å lagre <xref:System.Windows.Media.Geometry>objekter.</xref:System.Windows.Media.Geometry> </xref:System.Windows.Media.GeometryCollection>

trans-unit.source: Gets or sets how the intersecting areas of the objects contained in this <xref href="System.Windows.Media.GeometryGroup"></xref> are combined.
trans-unit.target: Henter eller angir hvordan kryssende områdene objektene finnes i dette <xref href="System.Windows.Media.GeometryGroup"> </xref> kombineres.

trans-unit.source: **EvenOdd** Determines the "insideness" of a point on the shape by drawing a ray from that point to infinity in any direction and counting the number of path segments from the given shape that the ray crosses.
trans-unit.target: **EvenOdd** bestemmer "insideness" til et punkt på formen ved å tegne et ray fra dette tidspunktet til uendelig i en retning og telle antall banen segmenter fra den angitte figuren ray krysser.

trans-unit.source: If this number is odd, the point is inside; if even, the point is outside.
trans-unit.target: Hvis dette antallet er et oddetall, er punktet i; Hvis punktet er jevne, utenfor.

trans-unit.source: **NonZero** Determines the "insideness" of a point on the shape by drawing a ray from that point to infinity in any direction and then examining the places where a segment of the shape crosses the ray.
trans-unit.target: **Ikke-null** bestemmer "insideness" til et punkt på formen ved å tegne et ray fra dette tidspunktet til uendelig i en retning og undersøker steder der et segment for formen krysser ray.

trans-unit.source: Starting with a count of zero, add one each time a Segment crosses the ray from left to right and subtract one each time a path segment crosses the ray from right to left.
trans-unit.target: Starter med et antall null, legger du til en hver gang et Segment krysser ray fra venstre mot høyre og trekk fra én hver gang en bane segmentet krysser ray fra høyre mot venstre.

trans-unit.source: After counting the crossings, if the result is zero then the point is outside the path.
trans-unit.target: Når telle crossings, hvis resultatet er null punktet er utenfor banen.

trans-unit.source: Otherwise, it is inside.
trans-unit.target: Hvis ikke, den er i.

trans-unit.source: The default value is `EvenOdd`.
trans-unit.target: Standardverdien er `EvenOdd`.
